The cottage to you seems impractical as a place to live as it has none of the basic amenities that might be needed - like a place to cook or fireplace for comfort on chilly evenings. For lack of anything else to inspect, you examine the furniture hoping to find a hint as to what this place is all about. It seems a useless exercise. But then beneath the table you notice a large vent. This makes no sense since you certainly wouldn’t expect an old place like this to have a forced air heating or cooling system. You remove the vent cover and while on your hands and knees listen carefully. There is a gentle breeze coming from the vent and almost imperceptibly the distinct humm of machinery. Now this is curious. The vent might just be big enough to crawl through…
